==English==
===Etymology===
From Adolf Brix, a German chemist
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Brix'''
# a [[measure]] (in [[degree]]s) of the amount of [[dissolved]] [[solid]]s in a [[liquid]] via its [[specific gravity]]; used especially to measure dissolved [[sugar]] in [[fruit juice]] and [[wine]]
